        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 25 at 2:09PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 208 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers near Athens,
or 7 miles north of Catskill, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hudson, Coxsackie, Valatie, Athens, Kinderhook, Lorenz Park,
Stockport, Stuyvesant, Stuyvesant Falls, Columbiaville, West
Coxsackie, Rossman, Result, Earlton, Otter Hook, Stockport Station,
Limestreet, Climax, Brick Tavern, and Sunnyside.

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 21 and 21B.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
